- Mm-hmm. Wait, wait, wait, wait.

973
01:06:03,711 --> 01:06:06,680
That's it.

974
01:06:08,483 --> 01:06:10,417
- I gotta tell Carin.
- What?

975
01:06:10,485 --> 01:06:12,112
Oh.

976
01:06:12,186 --> 01:06:14,620
- Can I borrow this stuff?
- Sure.

977
01:06:26,255 --> 01:06:28,621
- What do you see?
- Patch, it's late.

978
01:06:28,691 --> 01:06:31,091
What do you see?

979
01:06:31,160 --> 01:06:33,685
Parsley.

980
01:06:33,763 --> 01:06:35,697
- And a horn.
- No, no, no.

981
01:06:35,765 --> 01:06:38,791
Look beyond the objects.
Look through them.

982
01:06:38,868 --> 01:06:41,962
Over here. Look.

983
01:06:42,037 --> 01:06:44,767
Kind of let them blur.
Tell me the first thing you see.

984
01:06:44,840 --> 01:06:47,104
- Something with a nose.
- Okay.

985
01:06:47,176 --> 01:06:49,838
Now imagine that's a building
with a nose.

986
01:06:49,912 --> 01:06:53,177
- A free hospital.
- A free hospital.

987
01:06:53,249 --> 01:06:55,183
- Can I go back to bed now?
- No, no.

988
01:06:55,251 --> 01:06:57,719
Because I'm bursting with ideas,
and I need you to help me.

989
01:06:57,787 --> 01:07:00,950
It'll be the first fun hospital
in the world.

990
01:07:01,023 --> 01:07:03,116
It'll be a totally
free-form building.

991
01:07:03,192 --> 01:07:06,525
It'll have, like, slides
and secret passageways and game rooms.

992
01:07:06,595 --> 01:07:09,428
- Slow down. I can't write that fast.
- I can't slow down.

993
01:07:09,498 --> 01:07:12,558
We'll use humor
to heal pain and suffering.

994
01:07:12,635 --> 01:07:15,331
Doctors and patients
will work side-by-side as peers.

995
01:07:15,404 --> 01:07:18,066
There'll be no titles,
no bosses.

996
01:07:18,140 --> 01:07:22,406
People will come from all over
the world to fulfill their dream
of helping other people.

997
01:07:22,478 --> 01:07:24,946
They'll be a community
where joy is a way of life...

998
01:07:25,014 --> 01:07:29,280
where learning is the highest aim,
where love is the ultimate goal.

999
01:07:29,351 --> 01:07:32,718
- You have all that?
- Yeah, not verbatim, but
the overall insanity's intact.

1000
01:07:32,788 --> 01:07:34,722
- That's why you have to help me.
- Patch, no.

1001
01:07:34,790 --> 01:07:36,587
- Yes.
- No.

1002
01:07:36,659 --> 01:07:40,322
I know it's not gonna be easy, but you
said anything worth doing is difficult.

1003
01:07:40,396 --> 01:07:42,523
Look, um--

1004
01:07:42,598 --> 01:07:45,260
I'm not like you, Patch.

1005
01:07:45,334 --> 01:07:48,497
I want the white coat. I want people
to call me doctor more than anything.

1006
01:07:48,571 --> 01:07:52,701
- I want the recognition.
- You'll get it every day in the
eyes of patients you're helping.

1007
01:07:52,775 --> 01:07:56,370
There is more to life than
what Dean Walcott puts out there.

1008
01:07:56,445 --> 01:08:00,506
That is all about power
and control, all right?

1009
01:08:00,583 --> 01:08:03,143
- I know you're scared.
- You're right. I am scared.

1010
01:08:03,219 --> 01:08:05,153
I'm scared to death.

1011
01:08:08,657 --> 01:08:12,889
You know, you sit here and you talk
about life without limits...

1012
01:08:12,962 --> 01:08:15,829
you know,
and breaking the rules.

1013
01:08:15,898 --> 01:08:18,833
It all sounds
very, very romantic.

1014
01:08:20,436 --> 01:08:23,667
You wanna know what the truth
is about all that crap, Patch, hmm?

1015
01:08:23,739 --> 01:08:26,401
People get hurt.

1016
01:08:28,410 --> 01:08:30,344
And who did it to you?

1017
01:08:34,483 --> 01:08:37,975
- I have to go.
- No, don't. Please. No, no.
Listen to me. Come on.

1018
01:08:38,053 --> 01:08:40,248
Whatever it is-- Come on.
You can tell me.

1019
01:08:40,322 --> 01:08:42,756
- I can help you. I swear I can.
- Good night. I'll see you tomorrow.

1020
01:08:42,825 --> 01:08:45,885
Please, let me help you.

1021
01:08:45,961 --> 01:08:48,896
I'm really starting to love
the back of your head.

1022
01:09:08,217 --> 01:09:11,778
Get this cleaned out,
and get him down to the suture room.

1023
01:09:11,854 --> 01:09:13,788
You're gonna be fine, Larry.

1024
01:09:15,424 --> 01:09:18,393
Larry's been in and out of
the E.R. for a couple of years.

1025
01:09:18,460 --> 01:09:21,725
- Not because he's accident-prone.
- No. His father died two years ago.

1026
01:09:21,797 --> 01:09:24,994
Since then he's been subject to fits
of depression and self-mutilation.

1027
01:09:25,067 --> 01:09:27,262
Head trauma, D-5.

1028
01:09:31,006 --> 01:09:34,874
- Thank you for doing this.
- You can thank me
by not getting me fired.

1029
01:09:34,944 --> 01:09:38,675
Just observe rounds
and stay within hospital protocol.

1030
01:09:38,747 --> 01:09:40,681
Look, Patch.

1031
01:09:40,749 --> 01:09:43,411
You're a good thing
for this hospital.

1032
01:09:43,485 --> 01:09:45,680
You remind me of myself
when I first started out--

1033
01:09:45,754 --> 01:09:48,188
on fire,
wanting to save the world.

1034
01:09:48,257 --> 01:09:50,953
But you lose a little of that
after a while.

1035
01:09:51,026 --> 01:09:53,824
The system is what it is. It's not
perfect, but it's all we have.

1036
01:09:53,896 --> 01:09:57,855
Why does it have to be all we have?
Why can't it be changed?

1037
01:09:57,933 --> 01:10:00,834
You figure out how, Patch...

1038
01:10:00,903 --> 01:10:02,837
and I'll be there for you.

1039
01:10:02,905 --> 01:10:06,932
Bed six
needs blood work.

1040
01:10:07,009 --> 01:10:09,944
Mrs. O'Bannon
needs blood work.

1041
01:10:11,146 --> 01:10:14,138
Hello, Ed.
You feeling a little dizzy?

1042
01:10:14,216 --> 01:10:16,650
- Yeah.
- Hello, Mrs. O'Bannon.

1043
01:10:16,719 --> 01:10:19,984
- May I call you Catherine?
We're gonna draw a little blood.
- Mm-hmm.

1044
01:10:20,055 --> 01:10:22,853
Can you tell how many fingers
I'm holding up?

1045
01:10:24,727 --> 01:10:26,661
How many do you see?

1046
01:10:26,729 --> 01:10:28,663
How many fingers?

1047
01:10:32,668 --> 01:10:35,102
- How many fingers do you see, Ed?

1048
01:10:45,247 --> 01:10:47,738
How much longer do I have
to keep my eyes closed?

1049
01:10:47,816 --> 01:10:49,750
Just till I open mine.

1050
01:10:49,818 --> 01:10:51,979
Keep 'em closed.

1051
01:10:52,054 --> 01:10:54,648
You're almost there.

1052
01:11:03,365 --> 01:11:05,526
Not like that. This way.

1053
01:11:05,601 --> 01:11:08,092
Come on. Come on.

1054
01:11:08,170 --> 01:11:10,536
There you go.
All right.

1055
01:11:10,606 --> 01:11:13,473
Here, here.
Hold on to me.

1056
01:11:13,542 --> 01:11:15,669
It's just a little further.
Just a little further.

1057
01:11:15,744 --> 01:11:17,939
- All right, all right.
- There you go.

1058
01:11:18,013 --> 01:11:20,277
There you are.
That's all right.

1059
01:11:20,349 --> 01:11:22,283
- You're almost there.
- I'm afraid.

1060
01:11:22,351 --> 01:11:24,649
Don't be afraid.
It's gonna be worth it.

1061
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:27,188
All right. Ready?
Watch your step.

1062
01:11:27,256 --> 01:11:31,090
There you go.
And... open your eyes.

1063
01:11:33,162 --> 01:11:35,096
It's beautiful.

1064
01:11:35,164 --> 01:11:38,031
It's 105 acres
of all-natural forest.

1065
01:11:38,100 --> 01:11:41,797
Seven streams, two waterfalls.

1066
01:11:41,870 --> 01:11:45,306
This is it-- the future site
of the Gesundheit lnstitute.

1067
01:11:46,542 --> 01:11:48,476
This is yours?

1068
01:11:48,544 --> 01:11:51,945
Not yet,
but it will be soon.

1069
01:11:52,014 --> 01:11:54,448
- Come on. There's something else.
- Hmm?

1070
01:12:03,692 --> 01:12:05,626
What is it?

1071
01:12:06,829 --> 01:12:09,161
Our new home.

1072
01:12:09,231 --> 01:12:11,791
Carin, what do you think?

1073
01:12:12,868 --> 01:12:16,304
- How did you... find this?
- Him.

1074
01:12:16,371 --> 01:12:20,740
Arthur Mendelson. All this is his--
the land, the cottage.

1075
01:12:20,809 --> 01:12:23,175
He's letting us borrow it
till we can purchase it.

1076
01:12:23,245 --> 01:12:26,578
Mr. Mendelson, I realize that under
the terms of your commitment...

1077
01:12:26,648 --> 01:12:28,878
you retained control
of your assets.

1078
01:12:28,951 --> 01:12:31,613
- Nevertheless--
- You learn anything
about proctology yet, Patch?

1079
01:12:31,687 --> 01:12:33,621
- A little bit.
- Good.

1080
01:12:33,689 --> 01:12:36,157
Take care of this asshole
for me, will ya?

1081
01:12:36,225 --> 01:12:40,559
- Nice meeting you.
- Yeah. Mr. Mendelson, uh--

1082
01:12:40,629 --> 01:12:43,154
There's room for you.

1083
01:12:44,766 --> 01:12:47,599
- Hi, Bile.
- Hey, Patch.

1084
01:12:47,669 --> 01:12:49,728
- Who's Bile?
- An old friend.

1085
01:12:49,805 --> 01:12:52,273
- Oh.
- Without medical insurance.

1086
01:12:52,341 --> 01:12:54,809
He's just staying here
a couple of days.

1087
01:12:54,877 --> 01:12:57,311
What do you say?

1088
01:13:03,752 --> 01:13:05,686
Think potential.

1089
01:13:13,896 --> 01:13:17,889
Hey.

1090
01:13:29,478 --> 01:13:32,572
You're certainly a lovely couple.
We can't go on meeting like this.

1091
01:13:35,651 --> 01:13:37,585
Ma'am, this card is expired.

1092
01:13:37,653 --> 01:13:39,553
Have you a valid card?

1093
01:13:39,621 --> 01:13:43,387
Huh? Medicine.
Chinese medicine.

1094
01:14:24,233 --> 01:14:27,691
Yeah, yeah. That's painful there.

1095
01:14:27,769 --> 01:14:31,068
Uh, hang on a second.
I only have one arm.

1096
01:14:31,139 --> 01:14:33,073
Gesundheit.

1097
01:14:33,141 --> 01:14:36,372
- Let's go!
- Yeah. Uh-huh.

1098
01:14:38,313 --> 01:14:41,441
Uh-huh. Yeah.

1099
01:14:41,516 --> 01:14:44,815
Hi. How can we help you?

1100
01:14:45,888 --> 01:14:47,822
I don't know.

1101
01:14:47,890 --> 01:14:50,825
Uh, I h-heard about this place...

1102
01:14:50,893 --> 01:14:54,693
and l, I thought maybe
I would get some, uh--

1103
01:14:54,763 --> 01:14:57,960
You know, maybe I'd talk to somebody,
because my thoughts--

1104
01:14:58,033 --> 01:15:00,501
This is crazy.

1105
01:15:00,569 --> 01:15:03,367
Word's getting out
we're handling the overflow from
three different clinics now.

1106
01:15:03,438 --> 01:15:07,340
I start my pediatric clerkship
next week. I don't know how
I'm gonna... keep up.

1107
01:15:07,409 --> 01:15:10,401
Anybody call for a doctor in here?

1108
01:15:10,479 --> 01:15:12,743
Let's try this right now.
There. Look at that there.

1109
01:15:12,814 --> 01:15:16,079
Hey, thank you, Judy and Cissy,
for that lovely medicine.

1110
01:15:18,921 --> 01:15:22,789
- How you feeling, Frank?
You feel better?
- Yeah, feel better.

1111
01:15:22,858 --> 01:15:25,452
Well, keep on your medication. You can
never go wrong if you're a Marxist.

1112
01:15:25,527 --> 01:15:27,495
Hey, Patch?

1113
01:15:27,562 --> 01:15:29,553
- Yes?
- This is, um-- I didn't get your name.

1114
01:15:29,631 --> 01:15:32,293
- Uh, Larry.
- Hi, Larry. How are you?

1115
01:15:32,367 --> 01:15:34,494
- Good.
- Nice to meet you.

1116
01:15:34,569 --> 01:15:37,094
What are you passionate about, Larry?
What excites you?

1117
01:15:37,172 --> 01:15:39,697
- What turns you on?
- I like to read.

1118
01:15:39,775 --> 01:15:42,005
I love to read. What do you like
to read? Who's your favorite author?

1119
01:15:42,077 --> 01:15:44,443
- Mmm, Kazantzakis.
- Kazantzakis.

1120
01:15:44,513 --> 01:15:48,574
Oh. "World is trouble.
Man needs a little madness, or else--"

1121
01:15:48,650 --> 01:15:50,880
"Or else he dare not
cut the rope and be free."

1122
01:15:50,953 --> 01:15:52,887
That's great, Larry.
That's wonderful.

1123
01:15:52,955 --> 01:15:54,889
We're gonna get along just fine.
Truman.

1124
01:15:54,957 --> 01:15:58,120
- Yeah, Patch. What?
- Can you come over here
and show Larry around?

1125
01:15:58,193 --> 01:16:00,957
- Nice having you here, Larry. Welcome.
- Thanks. Okay.

1126
01:16:04,266 --> 01:16:08,134
- I've seen Larry in the E.R. before.
- He's weird.

1127
01:16:08,203 --> 01:16:11,604
I'm weird. If we don't
show him compassion, who will?

1128
01:16:17,879 --> 01:16:21,576
What's that name again? Right.

1129
01:16:43,105 --> 01:16:45,039
- Hi.
- Hi.

1130
01:16:56,351 --> 01:16:58,615
- Everyone asleep?
- Yeah.

1131
01:16:58,687 --> 01:17:00,621
But it ain't me.

1132
01:17:06,728 --> 01:17:08,662
You okay?

1133
01:17:11,266 --> 01:17:13,200
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

1134
01:17:18,206 --> 01:17:20,572
God, Patch, it's amazing.

1135
01:17:20,642 --> 01:17:22,576
What?

1136
01:17:22,644 --> 01:17:26,375
Just what you've done
with this place, you know.

1137
01:17:26,448 --> 01:17:28,882
- You too.
- Well.

1138
01:17:31,853 --> 01:17:33,787
These people
that we're helping--

1139
01:17:33,855 --> 01:17:36,289
they would have had
nowhere to go.

1140
01:17:38,693 --> 01:17:40,627
You're a good man.

1141
01:17:52,774 --> 01:17:55,072
What are we?

1142
01:17:56,578 --> 01:17:58,512
Is it me?

1143
01:18:01,616 --> 01:18:07,020
I mean, are we just-- are we
good friends that occasionally kiss?

1144
01:18:13,462 --> 01:18:16,226
Patch...

1145
01:18:16,298 --> 01:18:18,266
my entire life...

1146
01:18:18,333 --> 01:18:21,496
men have been...

1147
01:18:21,570 --> 01:18:23,538
attracted to me.

1148
01:18:28,743 --> 01:18:30,677
My entire life.

1149
01:18:40,589 --> 01:18:42,523
When I was a little girl...

1150
01:18:42,591 --> 01:18:45,526
I would look out my bedroom window
at the caterpillars.

1151
01:18:47,395 --> 01:18:49,329
I envied them so much.

1152
01:18:51,433 --> 01:18:53,367
No matter
what they were before...

1153
01:18:53,435 --> 01:18:56,871
no matter...
what happened to them...

1154
01:18:56,938 --> 01:19:01,807
they could just hide away,
you know...

1155
01:19:01,877 --> 01:19:05,973
and turn into these beautiful
creatures that could fly away...

1156
01:19:06,047 --> 01:19:07,981
completely untouched.

1157
01:19:16,525 --> 01:19:19,892
I hated men so much.

1158
01:19:25,233 --> 01:19:27,895
I wanted nothing
to do with them.

1159
01:19:42,284 --> 01:19:44,218
Then I met you.

1160
01:19:48,924 --> 01:19:51,859
The way that
you help people, Patch--

1161
01:19:54,462 --> 01:19:58,330
The changes I see
in everybody that's around you--

1162
01:20:13,982 --> 01:20:16,075
I love you.

1163
01:20:16,151 --> 01:20:20,178
I've loved you for so long.

1164
01:20:54,789 --> 01:20:58,122
You scared me.

1165
01:20:58,193 --> 01:21:00,991
I was watching you sleep.

1166
01:21:01,062 --> 01:21:04,793
I have a real knack.
Impressive, hmm?

1167
01:21:07,569 --> 01:21:10,561
"I love you
without knowing how...

1168
01:21:10,639 --> 01:21:12,937
"or when or from where.

1169
01:21:13,008 --> 01:21:15,169
- I love you straight--"
- Patch.

1170
01:21:17,946 --> 01:21:19,811
Um, sorry.

1171
01:21:19,881 --> 01:21:21,678
It's okay.

1172
01:21:21,750 --> 01:21:24,241
Uh, we have a situation
out here...

1173
01:21:24,319 --> 01:21:26,253
that needs attention.

1174
01:21:30,859 --> 01:21:33,293
I've been trying
to warn you guys about this...

1175
01:21:33,361 --> 01:21:35,295
and now we have
absolutely zero supplies.

1176
01:21:35,363 --> 01:21:37,797
There's an older gentlemen over there.
He has a sprained shoulder.

1177
01:21:37,866 --> 01:21:41,461
I don't have any slings.
I had to wrap his arm in his own belt.

1178
01:21:41,536 --> 01:21:44,903
We have no iodine. We don't even
have any gauze, for God's sake.

1179
01:21:46,274 --> 01:21:49,539
There's an entire supply room
at the hospital.

1180
01:21:49,611 --> 01:21:53,103
That couldn't possibly be because
those supplies belong to the hospital.

1181
01:21:53,181 --> 01:21:55,615
No.
That's too obvious.

1182
01:21:57,085 --> 01:22:01,522
Come on.
I need your feet, and I want your body.

1183
01:22:01,589 --> 01:22:03,614
- Come on.
- Bye.

1184
01:22:03,692 --> 01:22:05,319
Behave.

1185
01:22:05,393 --> 01:22:08,453
- Would you hurry, please?
This stuff is crushing me.
- Quiet. You're a corpse.

1186
01:22:08,530 --> 01:22:10,464
Ow!
Shh!

1187
01:22:10,532 --> 01:22:12,466
- Ow!
- Damn it!

1188
01:22:12,534 --> 01:22:16,129
- Watch it!
- Quiet. Shut up!

1189
01:22:56,188 --> 01:23:00,215
Yeah, uh, this is Larry.

1190
01:23:00,292 --> 01:23:03,921
Uh, I was wondering i-if
somebody could come over.

1191
01:23:03,995 --> 01:23:05,929
Uh--

1192
01:23:06,998 --> 01:23:09,091
I'm not doin' too well.
Um--

1193
01:23:10,802 --> 01:23:14,499
I was, I was-- I-lt would help
if I could talk to somebody.

1194
01:23:14,573 --> 01:23:17,371
Uh... okay.

1195
01:23:46,805 --> 01:23:48,739
Hello?

1196
01:23:59,885 --> 01:24:01,819
Larry?

1197
01:24:26,545 --> 01:24:28,479
Larry?

1198
01:24:30,482 --> 01:24:32,416
Are you okay?

1199
01:24:35,153 --> 01:24:39,112
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I'm fine. I'm fine.

1200
01:24:41,193 --> 01:24:44,754
- I didn't know you could play.
You sound wonderful.
- Thank you.

1201
01:24:44,830 --> 01:24:48,197
And this house-- it's amazing.
Is it yours?

1202
01:24:49,334 --> 01:24:51,768
It's my father's.
He left it to me.

1203
01:24:53,572 --> 01:24:55,506
Here.
Let me take your jacket.

1204
01:24:57,576 --> 01:24:59,510
Sure.

1205
01:25:02,180 --> 01:25:05,308
- You okay?
- Yeah. I'm fine. I'm fine.

1206
01:25:06,885 --> 01:25:09,319
Uh, come in.
Come in.

1207
01:25:10,288 --> 01:25:12,222
Thanks.

1208
01:25:14,292 --> 01:25:18,319
I really can't stay very long.
I just wanted to see how you were doing.

1209
01:25:19,564 --> 01:25:22,124
Yeah, you're right.

1210
01:25:24,903 --> 01:25:26,996
No, we don't wanna be late.

1211
01:25:40,285 --> 01:25:42,515
Patch.

1212
01:25:42,587 --> 01:25:44,646
- Oh.
- You just got a telephone call.

1213
01:25:44,723 --> 01:25:47,851
Dean Anderson wants to see you
in his office immediately.

1214
01:25:47,926 --> 01:25:52,829
- Oh, no. Walcott found out
about our borrowed supplies.
- We're dead.

1215
01:25:52,898 --> 01:25:55,230
Ye of little faith.

1216
01:26:03,708 --> 01:26:07,474
Dean Anderson, I know what this is
all about, and I assure you, sir--

1217
01:26:07,546 --> 01:26:09,480
Sit down.

1218
01:26:16,021 --> 01:26:18,455
Something happened last night.

1219
01:26:20,859 --> 01:26:22,793
Carin Fisher was murdered.

1220
01:26:25,597 --> 01:26:27,963
She was with Lawrence Silver.

1221
01:26:29,601 --> 01:26:32,729
There was a shotgun involved,
and then he turned the gun on himself.

1222
01:26:34,105 --> 01:26:37,632
Jesus Christ, Patch, I'm sorry.
I know she was a friend.

1223
01:26:38,710 --> 01:26:42,544
If there's, um,
anything I can do--

1224
01:26:47,018 --> 01:26:48,952
Hell of a deal.

1225
01:26:54,859 --> 01:26:57,953
"Into Your hands, O Merciful Savior...

1226
01:26:58,029 --> 01:27:00,862
we commend
Your servant Carin.

1227
01:27:00,932 --> 01:27:03,958
Receive her into the arms
of Your mercy,

1228
01:27:04,035 --> 01:27:07,493
into the blessed rest
of everlasting peace,

1229
01:27:07,572 --> 01:27:13,135
and into the glorious company
of the saints... on high."

1230
01:27:13,211 --> 01:27:15,645
Amen.

1231
01:28:10,268 --> 01:28:12,702
Told you I'd finish it
some other time.

1232
01:28:14,439 --> 01:28:16,373
Guess now's okay.

1233
01:28:19,911 --> 01:28:24,678
"I love you without knowing
how... or when...

1234
01:28:24,749 --> 01:28:26,683
or from where.

1235
01:28:29,087 --> 01:28:34,115
I love you straightforwardly,
without complexities or pride.

1236
01:28:34,192 --> 01:28:37,923
I love you because I know
no other way than this.

1237
01:28:40,231 --> 01:28:42,529
So close...

1238
01:28:42,600 --> 01:28:45,763
that your hand on my chest
is my hand.

1239
01:28:47,505 --> 01:28:50,303
So close
that when you close your eyes...

1240
01:28:51,876 --> 01:28:53,867
I fall asleep."

1241
01:29:06,091 --> 01:29:08,753
I'm sorry, honey! I'm sorry!

1242
01:29:18,703 --> 01:29:21,103
We can't disband.
You know that, right?

1243
01:29:22,540 --> 01:29:24,872
What about our patients?
What do we tell them?

1244
01:29:24,943 --> 01:29:27,639
They'll manage.
They managed before.

1245
01:29:27,712 --> 01:29:30,510
- I refuse to quit.
- Good.

1246
01:29:30,582 --> 01:29:33,176
God, you're being
so self-indulgent.

1247
01:29:33,251 --> 01:29:38,416
This has been your vision,
but we all built this place
and it belongs to all of us.

1248
01:29:38,490 --> 01:29:40,924
Carin will always remain
within these walls.

1249
01:29:40,992 --> 01:29:44,086
If you walk away from that,
if you let that all die--

1250
01:29:46,364 --> 01:29:48,832
I've dedicated
every spare moment I have...

1251
01:29:48,900 --> 01:29:53,269
to assisting you in what I believe
is a pure and a good purpose.

1252
01:29:53,338 --> 01:29:56,501
Quitting is not going
to help you get through this.

1253
01:29:56,574 --> 01:29:58,633
- You've always told us--
- Stop it!

1254
01:29:58,710 --> 01:30:01,077
I've always told you what?

1255
01:30:01,211 --> 01:30:04,612
People are good.
Trust people? Ha!

1256
01:30:04,681 --> 01:30:06,615
You know, Truman...

1257
01:30:06,683 --> 01:30:10,619
in all of God's creations, only
human beings kill their own species.

1258
01:30:10,687 --> 01:30:12,951
There's a fun fact
for your final exam.

1259
01:30:14,190 --> 01:30:18,024
Carin's death cannot make
helping people wrong.

1260
01:30:18,094 --> 01:30:20,722
She saw it coming.

1261
01:30:20,797 --> 01:30:24,460
She knew there was something dangerous
about Larry. I didn't see it.

1262
01:30:24,534 --> 01:30:26,968
Patch,
why are you being like this?

1263
01:30:27,037 --> 01:30:30,438
Because I killed her,
Truman.

1264
01:30:31,574 --> 01:30:34,543
I taught her the medicine
that killed her.

1265
01:30:42,419 --> 01:30:45,354
She'd still be here
if I hadn't met her.

1266
01:31:03,306 --> 01:31:05,240
You can't leave.

1267
01:31:08,378 --> 01:31:13,213
If what you say is true, looks like
I'm defying the laws of possibility.

1268
01:31:16,219 --> 01:31:18,153
What are you doing?

1269
01:31:19,489 --> 01:31:22,322
Oh, I can't leave
until you beat me, is that it?

1270
01:31:22,392 --> 01:31:24,451
Okay. I surrender.
You're number one.

1271
01:31:24,527 --> 01:31:28,327
You're the top student in the class.
You're smarter than me.

1272
01:31:28,398 --> 01:31:31,231
Is that what you want to hear?
Now can I leave?

1273
01:31:35,405 --> 01:31:38,602
You know Mrs. Kennedy
in 212?

1274
01:31:38,675 --> 01:31:40,609
She doesn't eat.

1275
01:31:40,677 --> 01:31:44,545
I visited her room every day
for the last three weeks.

1276
01:31:44,614 --> 01:31:46,548
I can't get her to eat.

1277
01:31:48,451 --> 01:31:51,716
Now, I know everything
there is to know about medicine.

1278
01:31:51,788 --> 01:31:53,722
I've studied relentlessly.

1279
01:31:53,790 --> 01:31:58,557
I guarantee you I can outdo,
outdiagnose any attending
and surgeon in this hospital.

1280
01:32:02,732 --> 01:32:04,666
But I can't make her eat.

1281
01:32:10,507 --> 01:32:13,135
You have a gift.

1282
01:32:13,209 --> 01:32:16,576
You have a way with people.

1283
01:32:16,646 --> 01:32:19,080
You know, they like you.

1284
01:32:21,785 --> 01:32:24,720
And if you leave,
I can't learn this way.

1285
01:32:41,438 --> 01:32:43,372
So what now, huh?

1286
01:32:44,974 --> 01:32:47,238
What do You want from me?

1287
01:32:53,416 --> 01:32:55,850
Yeah, I could do it.

1288
01:32:55,919 --> 01:32:58,854
We both know
You wouldn't stop me.

1289
01:33:03,193 --> 01:33:06,128
So answer me, please.

1290
01:33:06,196 --> 01:33:08,630
Tell me what You're doing.

1291
01:33:13,403 --> 01:33:15,837
Okay,
let's look at the logic.

1292
01:33:17,607 --> 01:33:19,632
You create man.

1293
01:33:19,709 --> 01:33:23,577
Man suffers enormous amounts
of pain.

1294
01:33:23,646 --> 01:33:27,013
Man dies.

1295
01:33:27,083 --> 01:33:31,144
Maybe You should have had just
a few more brainstorming sessions...

1296
01:33:31,221 --> 01:33:33,155
prior to Creation.

1297
01:33:34,757 --> 01:33:38,284
You rested
on the seventh day.

1298
01:33:38,361 --> 01:33:41,922
Maybe You should have spent
that day on compassion.

1299
01:33:51,040 --> 01:33:52,974
You know what?

1300
01:33:55,578 --> 01:33:57,512
You're not worth it.

1301
01:35:12,989 --> 01:35:15,321
Do you still want help
with Mrs. Kennedy?

1302
01:35:20,964 --> 01:35:23,364
Hey, Aggie.

1303
01:35:23,433 --> 01:35:25,867
We have a special
surprise for you.

1304
01:35:42,518 --> 01:35:46,352
Surprise!

1305
01:35:48,691 --> 01:35:51,159
Benvenuto, Aggie!

1306
01:35:51,227 --> 01:35:53,661
Aggie! Aggie!

1307
01:35:57,166 --> 01:35:59,134
Grab ahold, Aggie!

1308
01:35:59,202 --> 01:36:00,863
There you go.
Oh!

1309
01:36:00,937 --> 01:36:04,338
- Oh.
- Come on in, Aggie.!

1310
01:36:04,407 --> 01:36:06,341
Y-Yes.

1311
01:36:27,263 --> 01:36:29,857
Pasta angels, Aggie! Pasta angels!

1312
01:36:41,144 --> 01:36:43,408
Patch?

1313
01:36:43,479 --> 01:36:46,937
Hey. I'm supposed
to give you this.

1314
01:37:02,932 --> 01:37:06,197
- You turn around
and walk right out of here.
- Why?

1315
01:37:06,269 --> 01:37:09,170
Everything will be delineated
in your letter of dismissal.

1316
01:37:09,238 --> 01:37:11,900
- Why?
- You don't fit in.

1317
01:37:11,974 --> 01:37:13,999
There are standards
and codes.

1318
01:37:14,077 --> 01:37:17,171
You make the patients and everyone else
around you uncomfortable.

1319
01:37:17,246 --> 01:37:21,182
- I make you uncomfortable.
- Well, you can make this into
a personal issue if you'd like.

1320
01:37:21,250 --> 01:37:24,413
But the reality is,
you are not cut out to be a physician.

1321
01:37:24,487 --> 01:37:27,422
- And it is my responsibility--
- Responsibility?

1322
01:37:27,490 --> 01:37:31,620
You have one responsibility-- to be
a dick-head. How hard can that be?

1323
01:37:31,694 --> 01:37:35,221
All you have to do is make sure
your head is a dick
and it's attached to your neck.

1324
01:37:35,298 --> 01:37:37,493
- You leave immediately.
- I wanna see my records.

1325
01:37:37,567 --> 01:37:40,058
They're confidential.

1326
01:37:40,136 --> 01:37:42,001
Only the staff--

1327
01:37:47,744 --> 01:37:49,678
Please,
you have to have permission.

1328
01:37:49,746 --> 01:37:52,909
You can't just go in there
and take your own file!

1329
01:37:52,982 --> 01:37:54,916
Your marks are basically perfect.

1330
01:37:54,984 --> 01:37:58,442
You've gotta be near
the top of the class.

1331
01:37:58,521 --> 01:38:01,957
Look at this.
"Excessive happiness."

1332
01:38:02,024 --> 01:38:04,925
- Actually says
you're excessively happy?
- Mm-hmm.

1333
01:38:04,994 --> 01:38:07,554
And what does that mean?
lsn't that good?

1334
01:38:07,630 --> 01:38:11,726
- I gotta fight this.
- What can we do?

1335
01:38:11,801 --> 01:38:16,500
Dean Walcott seems thoroughly committed
to your not ever becoming a doctor.

1336
01:38:16,572 --> 01:38:19,063
Even Dean Anderson
signed this.

1337
01:38:20,843 --> 01:38:23,004
Nah, I'm screwed.

1338
01:38:23,079 --> 01:38:25,047
I like this.

1339
01:38:26,182 --> 01:38:28,116
You need my help.

1340
01:38:28,184 --> 01:38:30,550
I prefer to think
I'm using you.

1341
01:38:31,621 --> 01:38:33,555
- You have one shot.
- Mm-hmm.

1342
01:38:33,623 --> 01:38:36,592
- You'd have to appeal
to the state medical board.
- How does that work?

1343
01:38:36,659 --> 01:38:39,628
You claim that a prejudice
and injustice has occurred.

1344
01:38:39,695 --> 01:38:42,926
- They'll be worried about a suit.
They'll have to investigate.
- Then what?

1345
01:38:42,999 --> 01:38:45,968
- They'll review your grades,
which is good--
- Mm-hmm.

1346
01:38:46,035 --> 01:38:47,969
you're almost
top of the class--

1347
01:38:48,037 --> 01:38:49,971
but mostly your behavior.

1348
01:38:51,574 --> 01:38:54,099
Do you have any idea
what Walcott has on you?

1349
01:38:55,745 --> 01:38:57,679
How'd you get these?

1350
01:38:57,747 --> 01:39:00,580
Don't ask.

1351
01:39:00,650 --> 01:39:04,609
They can't prevent me
from graduating because of
a personality clash, can they?

1352
01:39:04,687 --> 01:39:06,951
Hunter, this is a medical institution
you're dealing with.

1353
01:39:07,023 --> 01:39:08,957
They draw their own law.

1354
01:39:09,025 --> 01:39:12,222
You'll have to get their focus
on your high marks and off of this.

1355
01:39:12,295 --> 01:39:14,229
I'm screwed, aren't l?

1356
01:39:15,798 --> 01:39:17,732
You're almost a doctor.

1357
01:39:17,800 --> 01:39:20,667
They're a panel of doctors.

1358
01:39:20,736 --> 01:39:24,467
Just think of them as your peers...
and return these.

1359
01:39:24,540 --> 01:39:26,371
Yeah.

1360
01:39:26,442 --> 01:39:29,878
And get a suit.

1361
01:39:54,270 --> 01:39:56,204
Hunter Adams.

1362
01:39:58,641 --> 01:40:01,906
You've been accused of
practicing medicine without a license.

1363
01:40:01,978 --> 01:40:04,276
That's a very
grave charge, son.

1364
01:40:04,347 --> 01:40:08,943
Are you aware that it's unlawful
to practice medicine without
a medical license?

1365
01:40:09,018 --> 01:40:10,679
Yes, sir, I am.

1366
01:40:10,753 --> 01:40:14,587
Are you aware that running a medical
clinic without the proper licensing...

1367
01:40:14,657 --> 01:40:16,921
can place both you
and the public...

1368
01:40:16,993 --> 01:40:19,086
in a great deal of danger?

1369
01:40:19,161 --> 01:40:21,129
Is a home a clinic, sir?

1370
01:40:21,197 --> 01:40:24,325
If you are admitting patients
and treating them...

1371
01:40:24,400 --> 01:40:26,868
physical location
is irrelevant.

1372
01:40:26,936 --> 01:40:30,702
Sir, will you define
treatment for me?

1373
01:40:30,773 --> 01:40:35,540
Yes. Treatment would be defined
as the care of a patient
seeking medical attention.

1374
01:40:36,746 --> 01:40:40,045
Have you been treating patients,
Mr. Adams?

1375
01:40:40,116 --> 01:40:43,108
I live with several people.
They come and go as they please.

1376
01:40:43,185 --> 01:40:45,119
I offer them
whatever help I can.

1377
01:40:45,187 --> 01:40:47,246
Mr. Adams...

1378
01:40:47,323 --> 01:40:51,419
have you or have you not
been treating patients at your ranch?

1379
01:40:53,462 --> 01:40:56,898
Everyone who comes to the ranch
is a patient, yes.

1380
01:40:59,902 --> 01:41:03,167
And every person who comes
to the ranch is also a doctor.

1381
01:41:05,174 --> 01:41:07,404
I'm sorry?

1382
01:41:07,476 --> 01:41:10,001
Every person who comes
to the ranch is in need...

1383
01:41:10,079 --> 01:41:12,809
of some form of physical
or mental help.

1384
01:41:12,882 --> 01:41:14,816
They're patients.

1385
01:41:14,884 --> 01:41:20,254
But also every person who comes
to the ranch is in charge of
taking care of someone else--

1386
01:41:20,322 --> 01:41:22,290
whether it's cooking for them,
cleaning them...

1387
01:41:22,358 --> 01:41:25,259
or even as simple a task
as listening.

1388
01:41:25,327 --> 01:41:27,261
That makes them doctors.

1389
01:41:27,329 --> 01:41:32,631
I use that term broadly, but is not a
doctor someone who helps someone else?

1390
01:41:32,701 --> 01:41:36,831
When did the term "doctor" get
treated with such reverence, as,
"Right this way, Doctor Smith"...

1391
01:41:36,906 --> 01:41:39,841
or, "Excuse me, Dr. Scholl,
what wonderful footpads"...

1392
01:41:39,909 --> 01:41:43,606
or, "Pardon me, Dr. Patterson,
but your flatulence has no odor"?

1393
01:41:46,348 --> 01:41:49,909
At what point in history
did a doctor become more...

1394
01:41:49,985 --> 01:41:54,217
than a trusted and learned friend
who visited and treated the ill?

1395
01:41:54,290 --> 01:41:57,453
Now, you ask me if
I've been practicing medicine.

1396
01:41:57,526 --> 01:42:00,620
Well, if this means opening
your door to those in need--

1397
01:42:00,696 --> 01:42:03,062
those in pain--

1398
01:42:03,132 --> 01:42:08,536
caring for them, listening
to them, applying a cold cloth
until a fever breaks--

1399
01:42:08,604 --> 01:42:10,902
if this is practicing medicine,
if this is treating a patient...

1400
01:42:10,973 --> 01:42:13,533
then I am guilty
as charged, sir.

1401
01:42:13,609 --> 01:42:17,204
Did you consider the ramifications
of your actions?

1402
01:42:17,279 --> 01:42:19,577
What if one of your patients
had died?

1403
01:42:19,648 --> 01:42:21,980
What's wrong
with death, sir?

1404
01:42:22,051 --> 01:42:24,519
What are we so mortally
afraid of?

1405
01:42:24,587 --> 01:42:27,852
Why can't we treat death with
a certain amount of humanity
and dignity and decency...

1406
01:42:27,923 --> 01:42:30,551
and, God forbid,
maybe even humor?

1407
01:42:30,626 --> 01:42:32,560
Death is not the enemy,
gentlemen.

1408
01:42:32,628 --> 01:42:35,563
If we're gonna fight a disease,
let's fight one of the most
terrible diseases of all--

1409
01:42:35,631 --> 01:42:37,565
indifference.

1410
01:42:37,633 --> 01:42:41,694
Now, I've sat in your schools and heard
people lecture on transference...

1411
01:42:41,770 --> 01:42:43,704
and professional distance.

1412
01:42:43,772 --> 01:42:46,263
Transference
is inevitable, sir.

1413
01:42:46,342 --> 01:42:48,867
Every human being
has an impact on another.

1414
01:42:48,944 --> 01:42:52,402
Why don't we want that in
a patient/doctor relationship?

1415
01:42:52,481 --> 01:42:56,884
That's why I've listened to your
teachings, and I believe they're wrong.

1416
01:42:56,952 --> 01:43:00,854
A doctor's mission should be
not just to prevent death...

1417
01:43:00,923 --> 01:43:03,050
but also to improve
the quality of life.

1418
01:43:03,125 --> 01:43:06,288
That's why you treat a disease,
you win, you lose.

1419
01:43:06,362 --> 01:43:11,595
You treat a person, I guarantee you,
you win, no matter what the outcome.

1420
01:43:13,569 --> 01:43:17,061
Now here today, this room
is full of medical students.

1421
01:43:17,139 --> 01:43:21,838
Don't let them anesthetize you.
Don't let them numb you out
to the miracle of life.

1422
01:43:21,911 --> 01:43:25,403
Always live in awe of the
glorious mechanism of the human body.

1423
01:43:25,481 --> 01:43:28,678
Let that be the focus of your studies
and not a quest for grades...

1424
01:43:28,751 --> 01:43:31,686
which'll give you no idea what kind
of doctor you will become.

1425
01:43:31,754 --> 01:43:33,847
Please try and address the board.

1426
01:43:33,923 --> 01:43:36,983
Don't wait till you're on the ward
to get your humanity back.

1427
01:43:37,059 --> 01:43:39,527
Start your interviewing skills.
Start talking to strangers.

1428
01:43:39,595 --> 01:43:42,291
Talk to your friends,
Talk to wrong numbers, everyone.

1429
01:43:42,364 --> 01:43:45,231
- Mr. Adams!
- And cultivate friendships...

1430
01:43:45,301 --> 01:43:48,600
with those amazing people in the back of
the room-- nurses that could teach you.

1431
01:43:48,671 --> 01:43:51,799
They've been with people every day.
They wade through blood and shit.

1432
01:43:51,874 --> 01:43:55,833
They have a wealth of knowledge,
and so do the professors you respect--

1433
01:43:55,911 --> 01:43:58,141
the ones who are not dead
from the heart up.

1434
01:43:58,214 --> 01:44:02,082
- Share their compassion.
Let that be contagious.
- Mr. Adams.

1435
01:44:02,151 --> 01:44:04,585
I demand that you turn
and address the board.

1436
01:44:04,653 --> 01:44:07,588
Sir, I want to be a doctor
with all my heart.

1437
01:44:20,069 --> 01:44:23,334
I wanted to become a doctor
so I could serve others...

1438
01:44:23,405 --> 01:44:25,873
and because of that
I've lost everything...

1439
01:44:25,941 --> 01:44:28,637
but I've also
gained everything.

1440
01:44:28,711 --> 01:44:32,875
I've shared the lives of patients
and staff members at the hospital.

1441
01:44:32,948 --> 01:44:35,883
I've laughed with them.
I've cried with them.

1442
01:44:37,253 --> 01:44:39,687
This is what I want to do
with my life.

1443
01:44:42,191 --> 01:44:44,955
And as God is my witness...

1444
01:44:45,027 --> 01:44:47,461
no matter what your decision
today, sir...

1445
01:44:47,529 --> 01:44:52,466
I will still become the best damn doctor
the world has ever seen.

1446
01:44:54,670 --> 01:44:57,730
Now you have the ability
to prevent me from graduating.

1447
01:44:57,806 --> 01:45:02,004
You can keep me from getting
the title and the white coat.

1448
01:45:02,077 --> 01:45:04,341
But you can't control
my spirit, gentlemen.

1449
01:45:04,413 --> 01:45:08,179
You can't keep me from learning.
You can't keep me from studying.

1450
01:45:08,250 --> 01:45:11,378
So you have a choice-- you could
have me as a professional colleague...

1451
01:45:11,453 --> 01:45:13,387
passionate...

1452
01:45:13,455 --> 01:45:16,754
or you can have me as an
outspoken outsider, still adamant.

1453
01:45:16,825 --> 01:45:19,885
Either way, I'll probably
still be viewed as a thorn.

1454
01:45:19,962 --> 01:45:22,260
But I promise you one thing.

1455
01:45:22,331 --> 01:45:24,993
I am a thorn
that will not go away.

1456
01:45:28,003 --> 01:45:29,994
Is that all?

1457
01:45:32,308 --> 01:45:34,242
I hope not, sir.

1458
01:45:37,379 --> 01:45:39,574
We will adjourn briefly.

1459
01:46:25,327 --> 01:46:27,261
Thank you.

1460
01:46:59,341 --> 01:47:01,070
Hunter Adams.

1461
01:47:05,848 --> 01:47:09,614
We find your methods
less than appealing.

1462
01:47:10,986 --> 01:47:13,921
Your appearance and your demeanor
do not reflect...

1463
01:47:13,989 --> 01:47:15,923
what we believe
is necessary...

1464
01:47:15,991 --> 01:47:19,085
to earn a patient's trust
and respect.

1465
01:47:20,562 --> 01:47:24,293
You openly accuse us of adhering
to time-honored practices...

1466
01:47:24,366 --> 01:47:29,167
that for years have been the backbone
of the entire medical institution.

1467
01:47:31,707 --> 01:47:33,868
However...

1468
01:47:33,943 --> 01:47:36,070
we find no fault
in your attempts...

1469
01:47:36,145 --> 01:47:39,603
to improve the quality of life
around you.

1470
01:47:40,849 --> 01:47:43,215
We find no fault
in your desire...

1471
01:47:43,285 --> 01:47:46,277
to expand upon existing
medical practices...

1472
01:47:46,355 --> 01:47:48,289
and theories.

1473
01:47:48,357 --> 01:47:51,986
We applaud your love
of the patient.

1474
01:47:52,061 --> 01:47:54,393
Your grades are among
the highest in your class...

1475
01:47:54,463 --> 01:47:57,523
and, therefore, we find
no merit in the decision...

1476
01:47:57,599 --> 01:48:00,500
to block your graduation
from medical school.

1477
01:48:07,476 --> 01:48:12,140
Now, along with your crass
and disdainful behavior...

1478
01:48:12,214 --> 01:48:15,377
you carry with you a flame...

1479
01:48:15,451 --> 01:48:17,385
which one could only hope...

1480
01:48:17,453 --> 01:48:20,479
would spread through
the medical profession like a brushfire.

1481
01:48:21,957 --> 01:48:23,891
And, uh, Dean Walcott...

1482
01:48:23,959 --> 01:48:27,053
in the future,
I think matters like this...

1483
01:48:27,129 --> 01:48:30,895
could best be solved if you yourself
would practice a little...

1484
01:48:30,966 --> 01:48:34,163
"excessive happiness."

1485
01:49:01,430 --> 01:49:03,591
Well, today you go...

1486
01:49:03,665 --> 01:49:07,294
from being students in a class
to being members of a class--

1487
01:49:07,369 --> 01:49:10,099
a very select class.

1488
01:49:10,172 --> 01:49:13,835
You face the future
with your heads held high...

1489
01:49:13,909 --> 01:49:16,707
because you are now...
doctors.

1490
01:49:26,555 --> 01:49:28,648
Dr. Michael Ames.

1491
01:49:34,229 --> 01:49:37,221
Dr. Doris Ackerman

1492
01:49:40,936 --> 01:49:43,666
Dr. Hunter "Patch" Adams.

1493
01:49:48,177 --> 01:49:50,338
Yea, Patch!

1494
01:49:53,916 --> 01:49:57,010
Well, I'm happy to see
you've finally decided to conform.

1495
01:49:57,086 --> 01:49:59,486
More than you know, sir.

